	abstract = {Estimates of the possibility of using heat pumps for heating classrooms of a metro school are given. The results of the numerical study of thermodynamic cascade-thermal-circuit efficiency of a heat pump installation are presented. The optimal cycle parameters for the working mediums, namely R407c and R134a refrigerants in the temperature range of 21-105°C are determined. The possibility of using a heat pump installation in traditional heating systems of buildings in the presence of a geothermal heat supply source is shown. A comparison with other technical solutions has been made. High-temperature HPUs can be widely used in industry, in drying processes of various materials (cement, clay, sand, wood, wastewater treatment waste). The paper presents the results of calculation studies and optimization of heat pump characteristics for the conditions of heating of underground premises of the school. The ground temperature at a depth of 10-12 m is 12-15C, which allows to use the ground heat as a heat source. Comparison with other technical solutions is made. The paper shows that the heating capacity in the upper cycle is 188.3 kW, compressor power is 54.8 kW, thermal efficiency is 0.39, conversion factor is 3.44. The exergy efficiency of the HPU is 0.626. The data of justification and selection of thermal scheme and capacity of HPU are given. © 2025 Author(s).},
