	affiliations = {Nanjing University of Aeronautics and Astronautics, College of Energy and Power Engineering, Nanjing, Jiangsu, China; Jiangsu Leke Thermal Technology Limited Company, Taizhou, Jiangsu, China},
	abstract = {In order to reflect the exergy of mechanical vapor recompression(MVR) ammonium sulfate wastewater treatment system and improve the system efficiency, the system was analyzed by the exergy method based on the second law of thermodynamics. The exergy methods were built up with the ammonium sulfate wastewater as actual solution. By using the actually measured operational data, the system was analyzed. The effects of parameters such as compression ratio, evaporation temperature and discharging concentration of one-effect, on exergy efficiency were studied and some proposals to improve the efficiency were put forward. The results show that the total exergy efficiency of the system is about 12.04%, the exergy losses of heat exchangers and compressors are the most and the exergy losses of them share about 79.5%. The parameters analysis shows that the system exergy efficiency decreases with compression ratio increasing and increases with evaporation temperature rising. Under the permission conditions, smaller compression ratio compressor and higher evaporation temperature should be used; under the conditions in this work, exergy efficiency is the maximum when the discharge mass concentration of one-effect is about 32%, so discharging feeds should be maintained at its mass concentration. The exergy efficiency can be raised by eliminating steam superheat.},
