	affiliations = {Hydro-Québec, Montreal, QC, Canada},
	abstract = {An approach to evaluate the exergy content of a hot waste stream is presented. Exergy is a thermodynamic property and exergy is related to the well-known thermodynamic properties enthalpy and entropy. Numerous types of apparatus have been proposed for the conversion of low-temperature heat into useful work using the thermodynamic cycles of heat engines and the total power out-put of such systems will be lower than the available work potential. A lot of heat, in the industrial sector, is simply discarded into the environment because it is considered as not useful for a specific process, but a hot stack gas, a residual low-pressure stream or even a hot waste-water stream, all have the potential to produce electricity. Exergy analysis can also be used to improve the efficiency of a process or to pinpoint and quantify imperfections for a given process, apart from computing the fraction of the thermal energy which can be converted to motive power.},
