	affiliations = {Delft University of Technology, Delft, Zuid-Holland, Netherlands},
	abstract = {Three process chains for waste water treatment sludge (dedicated waste incineration, and co-incineration in a power plant and a cement kiln, respectively) are compared on the basis of energy demand and exergy loss. Dedicated incineration has the lowest energy demand, but yields no useful product. When the saving in fossil energy due to the co-incineration is taken into account, these chains prove to be preferable. However, no distinction between the two co-incineration chains can be made on the basis of energy or exergy analysis alone. The use of sludge in co-incineration processes is advantageous, provided environmental safety standards are met.},
